{{Infobox person | name = Clara Berenbau | image = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = María Clara Berenbau Giuria | birth_date = {{Birth date|1980|11|07|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Montevideo]], Uruguay | death_date = {{Death date and age|2013|04|24|1980|11|07|df=yes}} | death_place = Montevideo, Uruguay | death_cause = [[Breast cancer]] | other_names = Clarita Berenbau | occupation = Presenter, announcer, columnist, actress, writer, journalist | years_active = | known_for = | notable_works = | spouse = Daniel Yaquinta | children = Salvador, Guadalupe | awards = [[Iris Award (Uruguay)|Iris Award]] | alma_mater = | website = {{URL|http://www.claritaberenbau.com}} }} '''María Clara Berenbau Giuria''' (7 November 1980 – 24 April 2013), also known as '''Clarita Berenbau''', was a [[Uruguay]]an presenter, announcer, columnist, actress, writer, and journalist.<ref name=sonrisa>{{Cite news |url=http://www.tvshow.com.uy/clarita-se-fue-queda-su-eterna-sonrisa.html |title=Clarita se fue, queda su eterna sonrisa |trans-title=Clarita Left, Her Eternal Smile Remains |work=[[El País (Uruguay)|El País]] |location=Montevideo |language=Spanish |date=25 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130425093923/http://www.tvshow.com.uy/clarita-se-fue-queda-su-eterna-sonrisa.html |archive-date=25 April 2013 |dead-url=yes |access-date=20 November 2017 |df= }}</ref>
==Biography== Clara Berenbau was born in [[Montevideo]] on 7 November 1980. In 2005, she married Daniel "Cuqui" Yaquinta at the La Candelaria Church in [[Punta del Este]]. They became parents of two children on 24 April 2012, Salvador and Guadalupe.
Berenbau worked in television and hosted the program ''Vamos'' on [[Teledoce]], as well as ''Cuatro Estaciones'' and ''Tiempo de Campo'' on [[Televisión Nacional Uruguay|Channel 5]]. She was a columnist for shows on the TV programs ''Hola Vecinos'' and ''Arriba Gente'' on [[Saeta TV Channel 10|Channel 10]]. On the radio she hosted ''Viva la Tarde''. In theater she starred in the play ''Estoy sola porque quiero''.<ref name=sonrisa/><ref name=lucha>{{Cite web |url=http://www.180.com.uy/articulo/32855_Murio-Clara-Berenbau |title=Murió Clara Berenbau |trans-title=Clara Berenbau Dies |work=180.com.uy |language=Spanish |date=24 April 2013 |access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref>
In 2007 she was diagnosed with [[breast cancer]]. Berenbau died in Montevideo on 24 April 2013, at age 32.<ref name=sonrisa/><ref name=lucha/>
==Awards== <!-- Can't find any sources for these: * 2004 and 2005 – Winner of the Joven Sobresaliente award for best host * 2008 – Taliche Award for investigative journalism * 2010 – Winner of the Woman of the Year award for best radio journalist * 2011 – Iris Award for best radio magazine for ''Viva la Tarde'' --> * 2007 and 2010 – [[Iris Award (Uruguay)|Iris Award]] for most elegant<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.republica.com.uy/fallecio-clara-berenbau/ |title=Falleció la joven comunicadora Clara Berenbau |trans-title=The Young Communicator Clara Berenbau Passed Away |work=republica.com.uy |language=Spanish |date=25 April 2013 |access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref> * 2012 – Iris Award for best radio host<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.elacontecer.com.uy/15820-noticia-2012-06-06.html |title=Destacados de la tv, radio, música y cine recibieron los premios Iris 2012 |trans-title=Greats of TV, Radio, Music and Film Receive 2012 Iris Awards |last=Fumero |first=Walter |work=elacontecer.com.uy |language=Spanish |date=6 June 2012 |access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref>
==Book== In 2011, Berenbau published the autobiography ''{{ill|Vivir con él|es}}'' (Palabra Santa, {{ISBN|9789974830813}}) detailing her struggle with cancer.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://historico.elpais.com.uy/suplemento/ds/vivir-con-la-cruz-del-cancer/sds_601322_111023.html |title=Vivir con la cruz del cáncer |trans-title=Living With the Cross of Cancer |last=Bluth |first=Daniela |work=[[El País (Uruguay)|El País]] |location=Montevideo |language=Spanish |date=23 October 2011 |access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://historico.elpais.com.uy/11/11/07/pespec_604746.asp |title='Vivir con él', de Clara Berenbau |trans-title='Living With It', by Clara Berenbau |work=[[El País (Uruguay)|El País]] |location=Montevideo |language=Spanish |date=7 November 2011 |access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref> She was writing a second book at the time of her death.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://eldiario.com.uy/2013/05/06/se-edita-libro-postumo-de-clarita-berenbau/ |title=Se edita libro póstumo de Clarita Berenbau |trans-title=Posthumous Book of Clarita Berenbau Published |work=El Diario |language=Spanish |date=6 May 2013 |access-date=20 November 2017}}</ref>
