 Park Press''|1975|p=9}} |- | 1975{{sfn|Sarmento|1975|p=30}} ! scope="row"| ''Floresta Amazonica'' | choreography Frederick Ashton, music by [[Heitor Villa-Lobos]]{{sfn|''The Asbury Park Press''|1975|p=9}} | female dancer | The pas de deux was created for Fonteyn by Ashton and performed by she and Nureyev in its US debut during November 1975 in ''Fonteyn & Nureyev on Broadway''.{{sfn|Sarmento|1975|p=30}} |- | 1975{{sfn|Sarmento|1975|p=30}} ! scope="row"| ''[[Le Corsaire Pas de Deux]]'' | choreography Marius Petipa, music by Adolphe Adam revised by Cesare Pugni, Léo Delibes, Riccardo Drigo and Petr Oldenbourg | female dancer | Performed by Fonteyn and Nureyev in ''Fonteyn & Nureyev on Broadway'' in November 1975.{{sfn|Sarmento|1975|p=30}} |- | 1976{{sfn|Royal Opera House|1965}} ! scope="row"| ''[[Romeo and Juliet (MacMillan)|Romeo and Juliet]]'' | choreography by Kenneth MacMillan, music by Sergei Prokofiev | Juliet | Performed by Fonteyn and Nureyev on 5 January, 6 January, and 10 January 1976.{{sfn|Royal Opera House|1965}} |- | 1976{{sfn|Royal Opera House|1976}} ! scope="row"| ''Amazon Forest pas de deux'' | choreography Frederick Ashton, music by Heitor Villa-Lobos | female dancer | Fonteyn danced with David Wall in the Royal Opera House Premier on 23 November 1976. The ballet had originally been titled ''Floresta Amazonica''.{{sfn|Royal Opera House|1976}} |- | 1977{{sfn|Royal Opera House|1942}} ! scope="row"| ''Hamlet'', prelude | choreography by Robert Helpmann, music by Tchaikovsky | Ophelia | Danced by Fonteyn on 30 May 1977.{{sfn|Royal Opera House|1942}} |- | 1979{{sfn|Royal Opera House|1979}} ! scope="row"| ''Salut d'amour à Margot Fonteyn'' | choreography by Frederick Ashton, [[Salut d'Amour|music]] by [[Edward Elgar]] | female dancer | Tribute written for Fonteyn by Ashton, the two who danced the roles, for her 60th birthday celebration.{{sfn|Royal Opera House|1979}} |- | 1979{{sfn|Percival|2008}} ! scope="row"| ''[[Façade (ballet)|Façade]]'' | choreograph